    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-wine-700 mb-2">What's the best wine to pair with both turkey and ham at Thanksgiving?</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700">Pinot Noir is the ultimate crowd-pleaser for mixed meat Thanksgiving tables, as its bright acidity and moderate tannins complement both turkey's lean protein and ham's saltiness. Alternatively, a dry Riesling or Gewürztraminer offers enough richness to stand up to ham while providing the crisp acidity that cuts through turkey's richness. These wines also pair beautifully with cranberry sauce and sweet potato casseroles.</p>
