  <div>
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-wine-700 mb-2">What wine works best for guests who don't usually drink wine?</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700">Off-dry Riesling or Moscato are excellent gateway wines for hesitant drinkers, offering just enough sweetness to appeal to unaccustomed palates while maintaining enough acidity to pair with food. These wines are approachable, fruit-forward, and won't intimidate guests with harsh tannins or overwhelming complexity. Serve them slightly chilled to enhance their refreshing qualities and food-pairing versatility.</p>
