    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-wine-700 mb-2">When should I open and decant my Thanksgiving wines?</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700">Open lighter wines like Pinot Noir and Beaujolais just 30 minutes before serving to let them breathe without losing their delicate aromatics. Heavier reds benefit from 1-2 hours of decanting, while white wines should be opened just before serving to preserve their crispness. Avoid decanting wines with significant sediment right before guests arrive, as this can create cloudy pours during the meal.</p>
